commit_message:
Fixing lost vlan ids on interfaces

Sometimes a vm gets its tap interface unset and reset too fast to be caught in
an agent loop, and its vlan tag was not reset.

We now detect if an interface loses its vlan tag, and if it happens the
interface will be reconfigured.

Since the TAG ID is only available via the "Port" table (in the 'tag' column),
we couldn't reuse the get_vif_port_set() method's run_vsctl call which queries
the "Interface" table, and needed a specific run_vsct call to the "Port" table
in the new get_port_tag_dict() method.

Conflicts:
	neutron/tests/unit/openvswitch/test_ovs_lib.py

Change-Id: I7f59e2c1e757c28dae35c44ebfad9d764ae1d3c5
Closes-Bug: 1240849
(cherry picked from commit 60cb0911712ad11688b4d09e5c01ac39c49f5aea)

commit_message:
Adds v2 keystone service test to service v3

This submission adds missing v3 tests in test_services.py
when compared with v2 test_services.py. Also added corresponding

commit_message:
Add a NotLockingAccounts credentials provider

This credentials provider does not do any locking, so it
does not suffer from the lack of credentials cleanup which
affects the regular locking Accounts class.

Using thie credentials provider allows to keep it possible
to run tempest with no tenant isolation, and in serial mode,
as it is done today by one of periodic jobs.

Partially-implements bp:test-accounts
Change-Id: I160d183a299d2e46d269428409af680c0fdb03b5

Nova v2 hypervisor server API return attribute "uuid" in response's

commit_message:
Fix V2 hypervisor server schema attribute

Nova v2 hypervisor server API return attribute "uuid" in response's
server dict. Current response schema does not have this attribute instead
it contain "id" which is wrong.

This patch fix the above issue.

NOTE- "uuid" attribute in this API response is always a uuid.

Change-Id: I78c67834de930012b70874938f345524d69264ba

commit_message:
Fix sample-create in v2 api calls

A dict embedded in a list is the expected input. In
47934c777c50897b649793e0960eebdaad322c45 the list was lost, this
puts it back.

Note that the _exact_ date of this failure was identified by
existing Rally jobs which started failing in early August. That made
searching the commit logs straightforward.

Change-Id: I37e794de7a23b8ce8e67a086732af5a19f182409
Closes-Bug: #1367867

commit_message:
Allow some translations to be made.

Transform some action_present and action_past variables from attributes to
methods with the solution proposed in this patch:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/91338/
Also fix a bug in the solution above where the __init__ function in the
deleteAction class overwrite the action_present and action_past methods.
Closes-Bug: 1366731

Change-Id: I9595f9d5a5a3f1ef4d528ddb3e08737a43471402

commit_message:
Make strutils.mask_password more secure

Make some enhancements to strutils.mask_password to allow it to
catch more cases of passwords in strings.

The following is a listing of patterns that will be handled. The
keyword that mask_password uses (a list of four now) is represented
by <key> and the password is shown as <password>. Quotes (both single
and double) are represented as <quote>.

--<key> <password>
--<key> <quote><password><quote>
<key> = <password>
<key> = <quote><password><quote>

All existing tests and patterns are still handled.

Cherry-pick from 61d5de69850bf082b2aa45747104b2b5be764c21
Partial-Bug: #1345233

Conflicts:
	nova/openstack/common/strutils.py

Change-Id: I693baaf225c5b393401d499d14f271cadb63eb2c

commit_message:
Initial kerberos plugin implementation.

This patch will allow to use kerberos credentials to retrieve
a token during a post on /v3/auth/tokens. It will force the negotiate
communication with the client if the method specified is kerberos
and leaves unaffected the other plugins.

bp: kerberos-authentication

Change-Id: I2fad67c3613c273187f6ca32985d360352c81bf8

commit_message:
Mask passwords in exceptions and error messages

When a ProcessExecutionError is thrown by processutils.execute(), the
exception may contain information such as password. Upstream
applications that just log the message (as several appear to do) could
inadvertently expose these passwords to a user with read access to the
log files. It is therefore considered prudent to invoke
strutils.mask_password() on the command, stdout and stderr in the
exception.

Cherry-pick from 853d8f9897f8563851441108a9be26b10908c076
Partial-Bug: #1343604

Conflicts:
	nova/openstack/common/processutils.py

Change-Id: I9741dcdebdb4bed295ddc5ec4c4b117fffcfe88c

I have to rework the patch.

Indeed, this::

        data_type = ungettext_lazy(
            self.data_type_singular,
            self.data_type_plural,
            count
        )

does not generate catalogue entries in the po files, and defining action_present_singular an action_present_plural on classes is wrong because this suposes there exists one singular and one plural, and this is false in many languages:
http://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/manual/html_node/Translating-plural-forms.html

Indeed, some languages have 3, 4 or 5 plural forms...

I found a way to handle this so a next patch is coming up soon.'}, {'account_id': 8674, 'date': '2014-05-20 10:09:54.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 6.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-05-20 10:09:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

Doug,

I tend to agree with you about table actions as one of I18N team members :-) except one point. I still think it is not an easy thing to require developers to add appropriate contextual markers. I believe *continuous* contributions from I18N team is required to make it work but I am not sure. (Personally I already have too many hats and cannot be fair.)

My concern is about status/task choices. Honestly speaking it is too ugly. As Yves commented in patch set 14, I hope it is addressed soon by the tool. Once it is achieved, it sounds practical to add "contextual markers" to status choices. I still disagree on status/task choices.

Are we in the same page? Thought?'}, {'account_id': 12699, 'date': '2014-09-03 13:17:03.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16: Code-Review+1'}, {'account_id': 9981, 'date': '2014-09-03 14:40:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16:

Akihiro:  We are largely on the same page.  

I'm actually not concerned about the contextual markers on the status/task choices.  I think its going to be easy enough for developers to copy the pattern if any new status/task choices are added.  I agree it does make that section of code more difficult to read, but IMO its not a tough section to understand anyway.  It's still within my arbitrary levels of "easily understandable" code.

It might be tidier if the description could be a constant, but there is no functional reason these all have to be word for word the same: they are contexts for different terms.

Just taking a quick glance at the terms, I'd expect "Shut Down", "Reboot", "Build" all require contextual markers.  They can be understood as both actions and states.  I assume it's necessary to have markers on these terms because in other languages the action and state that match "Build" for example won't always be the same term.  In all cases, I think its useful to put markers on these statuses and tasks because they are short phrases that might be hard to understand without context.

Input from the I18N team is going to be a critical part of making contextual markers work, but I think we have a number of developers who are aware of globalization issues and can catch some problems at code review time.

I'd still be happy to see this code merged in its current state.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-09-09 07:32:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16: Code-Review+1

	    action_present_singular = _(u"Hard Reboot Instance")	
	    action_present_plural = _(u"Hard Reboot Instances")

	    action_past_plural = _(u"Hard Rebooted Instances")

Hi Matthew.

please have a look here: https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/I18n/TranslatableStrings#Use_ungettext_for_pluralisation

I'm terribly sorry to say that (by experience) using action_present_singular and action_present_plural generates failing translations in many languages.
Indeed, some languages can reach 6 forms of plurals. It is a rule of thumb in translatable strings to never handle singular and plural in the code but to let ungettext do it (it's currently the only way to have the extra forms of plurals generated in their respective po files, e.g.: if you generate the Irish (Gaelic) po file you'll see 5 forms of plurals, and in Arabic you'll see 6 forms of plurals). The current method handled only 2 forms
Also, zero is plural in English, but singular in French, and different in many other languages, so the current way plural was handled just had to be removed because many of the translations of horizon where not feasible properly at all and where simply wrong. You can clearly see that to handle the plural properly requires using a different algorithm depending on the language, the complexity would be tremendous if we had to fix ourselves the _get_action_name method, but luckily, this complexity is already handled very well by ungettext.

We also need contextual markers for the following reason:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/I18n/TranslatableStrings#Use_contextual_markers_on_short_strings_to_avoid_ambiguousness
e.g.: "Shut Off" has different translations in French (and many languages).
The status of a "Shut Off" instance would be translated as "teinte", and the action to perform to Shut Off an instance would be "teindre" German also has these differences (even far more than French). without contextual markers in this example, the translation was currently failing in a case or the other (It's even worse in many other languages).

The reason we can not use variables or constants for contextual markers is that xgettext is an external program which will not execute the python code to evaluate a variable or constant (and probably never will, otherwise it'll also have to compile and execute C code and other languages, since it also generates po files for C and tons of other languages too)
xgettext is just a source code parser which generates po files and handles the different forms of plural and reads "strings" as contextual markers

More info:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/I18n/TranslatableStrings

Let me know if anything is unclear.
Regards,'}, {'account_id': 9659, 'date': '2014-09-09 22:42:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

Hey Yves-Gwenael Bourhis,

Perhaps an intermediate solution could be reached.  I'm thinking something like this:

[code]
class topInstance(tables.BatchAction):	
            action_context_marker = u"Action to perform"
	    action_present_singular = u"Shut Off Instance"	
	    action_present_plural = u"Shut Off Instances"	
	    action_past_singular = u"Shut Off Instance"
	    action_past_plural = u"Shut Off Instances"		
[code]

And then in the super-class, we could add in the action_context_marker and potentially append either " - past" or " - present" as necessary.

I THINK that would/could cover all the cases that show up in your code. (I'm comparing it to patch 17.)

Again, my intent is to move as much of the logic into the superclass to remove as much repeated code and logic from each and every subclass of batch action.'}, {'account_id': 8674, 'date': '2014-09-09 22:55:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

No, this fails to generate the proper po file.

I must precise also that we can not use variables pre-translated with gettext_noop or gettext_lazy or gettext to be passed to ungettext either.

This is because xgettext parses for "strings" passed to ungettext in order to generate the catalog of 2,3,4,5 or 6 plural forms (depending on the language).

If you pass to ungettext a variable which was added to the catalog by a gettext_noop (.e.g.), the extra forms of pluralization will be missing in the po file. and pluralization will simply generate broken translations unsolvable by the translator (the issue was happening in the first patch-sets, e.g. in patch-set 4).

This is why you *have* to pass strings to ungettext, otherwise the po file is not generated with multiple plural forms and the translation just can not be done properly (or not even at all) by translators.

The reason I implemented this way is because of the way the po files are generated, in order to have the proper catalog.

(patch-set 4 generated an unusable po catalog for multiple plural forms).

using variables as you mention leads to completely missing strings in the po files and the translation fails.

the problem is about po file generation, not of what seems logical.

just try it and you will see that with:

[code]
class topInstance(tables.BatchAction):	
            action_context_marker = u"Action to perform"
	    action_present_singular = u"Shut Off Instance"	
	    action_present_plural = u"Shut Off Instances"	
	    action_past_singular = u"Shut Off Instance"
	    action_past_plural = u"Shut Off Instances"		
[code]

the strings are purely ignored when generating the po file and are not even available for translation.'}, {'account_id': 9659, 'date': '2014-09-09 22:59:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 17: -Code-Review

Hrmmm.  Good point.  Yuck, this is just an ugly issue.  I'll remove my -1, but I'm still convinced that there's gotta be a better way.  :-)  I just don't know what it is."}, {'account_id': 8674, 'date': '2014-09-09 23:03:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 17:

[code]
ungettext('singular', 'plural', count)  # you have 5 strings to translate in the Irish po file, etc...
[code]

[code]
singular_variable = 'singular'
plural_variable = 'plural'
ungettext(singular_variable, plural_variable, count)  # zero strings to translate in the po file.
[code]

[code]
singular_variable = _('singular')
plural_variable = _('plural')
ungettext(singular_variable, plural_variable, count)  # two strings to translate in the po file, fails with multiple plural forms of 3,4, 5 and 6.
[code]

same issue with contextual marker, the contextual marker does not appear in the po file if it comes from a variable.

The issue is about generating the po file, not the logic."}, {'account_id': 8674, 'date': '2014-09-09 23:07:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 17:

[code]

[code]

    plural_variable = 'plural'

[code]

[code]

    plural_variable = _('plural')
    ungettext(singular_variable, plural_variable, count) # two strings to translate in the po file, fails with multiple plural forms of 3,4, 5 and 6.
[code]"}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-09-10 00:41:14.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

Hi Yves-Gwenael, 

I am not sure if I understand what you said. You mentioned that we can not use pre-translated variable. But if I use just a non translated variable to avoid repeating string like the following, will that be ok? 

STATUS_MARKER = "Current status of an Instance"

STATUS_DISPLAY_CHOICES = (
    ("deleted", pgettext_lazy(STATUS_MARKER, u"Deleted")),
    ("active", pgettext_lazy(STATUS_MARKER, u"Active")),'}, {'account_id': 8674, 'date': '2014-09-10 04:23:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

Hi Gloria,

Doing so fails, you will not have the contextual marker in the po file.

A contextual marker is a string the translator needs to see in the po file.

xgettext does not run the python code at all to generate the po file, it parses the python file for "strings", all that is not a pure string never goes in the po file.

So variables and constants, all fail at 100% to appear in the po file.

The issue here is the po file generation. If we want a string to be in the po file, it has to be a string somewhere in the source code too.

for pluralization you need this in a po file:

    msgid "Terminate Instance"                                                      
    msgid_plural "Terminate Instances"                                              
    msgstr[0] ""                                                                    
    msgstr[1] ""                                                                    
    msgstr[2] ""                                                                    
    msgstr[3] ""                                                                    
    msgstr[4] "" 

only strings will generate these seveveral msgstr in the Irish po file.

With contextual markers we have (french examlpe):
                                  
    msgctxt "Action to perform (the instance is currently running)"                 
    msgid "Shut Off Instance"                                                       
    msgid_plural "Shut Off Instances"                                               
    msgstr[0] "teindre l'instance"                                                 
    msgstr[1] "teindre les instances"

in the po file, we need a string in order to have msgctxt in the po file, constants and variables fail to generate the "msgctxt" line.

with pretranslated strings, variables or constants we don not have msgstr[0], msgstr[1], etc... for pluralization in the po file.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-09-10 05:04:36.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

Gloria, I commented the same as your comment in the past patch set. I tried to do it but it failed. Django makemessages (called by "./run_tests.sh --makemessages") fails to extract the contextual marker. This is the reason I say we need to improve django and/or gettext tools.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-09-10 05:18:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

Looks good, but there are a few things to be cleanup towards Juno release.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-09-10 07:42:45.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17: Code-Review+2

I am new to this I18N thingy...thanks Yves-Gwenael and Motoki-San for the clarification.'}, {'account_id': 8674, 'date': '2014-09-10 19:38:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 17:

(2 comments)

You're welcome Gloria.

You and Matthew had very relevant questions and suggestion, and when speaking "logic", I reacted exactly like you and Matthew for the first patch-sets before noticing that the po files where not generated properly, and pulled my hair off when I noticed that it didn't work as expected when using variables.

So I think https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/I18n/TranslatableStrings would need more clarifications about this (I will also add what Akihiro said in this thread which was of great help).

So I would really appreciate that you and Matthew add comments and suggestions in https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/i18n_translatable_strings so that I can update the related wiki page with what you think would clarify the subject and the reason why we can not use variables in this patch set.

Thanks all for your comments, I'll update the Wiki page as soon as possible. and add a new pat-set to address Akihiro's comments.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-09-11 09:46:42.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 17: Workflow+1

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-04-30 11:54:37.000000000', 'message': "Allow translators to translate BatchActions

Curently BatchAction proposes only an action_present and action_past verb
to be concatenated with a data_type_singular or data_type_plural

The issue is that many languages need to conjugate the verb with the
plural/singular subject, and some translations where terribly awfull and
impossible to do.

This patch introduces the action_present_singular, action_present_plural,
action_past_singular and action_past_plural attributes which in conjonction
with https://review.openstack.org/57701 allows better translation to be
performed

This patch also uses conextual markers in the translation which provide the
translators a context string allowing them to know in which context the
translation will take place.

We can't introduce contextual markers everywhere at once because Translators
would totaly loose their previous work. So we have to progressively introduce
contextual markers, when a string is changed, or for new strings. It is also
the reason why this patch changes only the string of the visible buttons.

Since we can't use contextual markers for all the code at once, this patch
partialy Closes-Bug: #1307476

Change-Id: I4cef42dc4a12f55cf750d9a18083254c6a96e716

"}, {'created': '2014-05-20 10:09:54.000000000', 'message': "Allow translators to translate BatchActions

Currently BatchAction proposes only an action_present and action_past verb
to be concatenated with a data_type_singular or data_type_plural string.

The issue is that many languages need to conjugate the verb with the
plural/singular subject, and some translations where terribly awfull and
impossible to do.
Indeed, some languages have up to 5 plural forms depending on the number of
items.

This patch introduces the fact that action_present is a method instead of an
attribute, which in conjonction with https://review.openstack.org/57701 allows
better translation to be performed.

It is important to use unicode strings with contextual markers because of the
following django bug:
https://code.djangoproject.com/ticket/22565
The django community was very quick and responsive and fixed the bug very fast:
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/142c27218a0bb07bb197faab7b1d8eb3a084f5b9
and back-ported their fix in the 1.6 and 1.7 django branches:
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/61fd00d4fd65f44d0a05be4c7e95124e4102ec27
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/034866204b39f797c73997b03cd90443aa03aa91
but since in horizon we support back to django 1.4, we will have to live with
it by providing unicode strings until we drop support of old django versions.

We can't introduce contextual markers and ungettext (pluralization) verywhere
at once because Translators would totally loose their previous work. So we have
to progressively introduce contextual markers and pluralization, when a string
is changed, or for new strings. It is also the reason why this patch changes
only the string of the visible buttons.

Since we can't use contextual markers and pluralization for all the code at
once, this patch partially:

Closes-Bug: #1307476

Change-Id: I4cef42dc4a12f55cf750d9a18083254c6a96e716

Currently BatchAction proposes only an action_present and action_past verb
to be concatenated with a data_type_singular or data_type_plural string.

The issue is that many languages need to conjugate the verb with the
plural/singular subject, and some translations where terribly awfull and
impossible to do.

items.

This patch introduces the fact that action_present is a method instead of an
attribute, which in conjonction with https://review.openstack.org/57701 allows
better translation to be performed.

This patch also adds contextual mrkers to STATUS_DISPLAY_CHOICES,
TASK_DISPLAY_CHOICES and POWER_DISPLAY_CHOICES because it was impossible to
translate the stand-alone words out of context for a translator (i.e. the word
"active" will be translated differently if the active object is feminine or
masculine, since feminine and masculine depends also on the language, it is
mission impossible for the translator to translate "active" if he does not know
"what" is "active").

It is important to use unicode strings with contextual markers because of the
following django bug:
https://code.djangoproject.com/ticket/22565
The django community was very quick and responsive and fixed the bug very fast:
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/142c27218a0bb07bb197faab7b1d8eb3a084f5b9
and back-ported their fix in the 1.6 and 1.7 django branches:
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/61fd00d4fd65f44d0a05be4c7e95124e4102ec27
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/034866204b39f797c73997b03cd90443aa03aa91
but since in horizon we support back to django 1.4, we will have to live with
it by providing unicode strings until we drop support of old django versions.

We can't introduce contextual markers and ungettext (pluralization) verywhere
at once because Translators would totally loose their previous work. So we have
to progressively introduce contextual markers and pluralization, when a string
is changed, or for new strings. It is also the reason why this patch changes
only the strings of the instance view actions.

This patch also fixes an issue where the status_class of a cell was set
depending on the post_translation of the cell status, therefore, in any
language other than english cells where in "status_unknown".

Since we can't use contextual markers and pluralization for all the code at
once, this patch partially:

Closes-Bug: #1307476

Change-Id: I4cef42dc4a12f55cf750d9a18083254c6a96e716

commit_message:
Allow translators to translate BatchActions

Currently BatchAction proposes only an action_present and action_past verb
to be concatenated with a data_type_singular or data_type_plural string.

The issue is that many languages need to conjugate the verb with the
plural/singular subject, and some translations where terribly awfull and
impossible to do.
Indeed, some languages have up to 5 plural forms depending on the number of
items.

This patch introduces the fact that action_present is a method instead of an
attribute, which in conjonction with https://review.openstack.org/57701 allows
better translation to be performed.

This patch also adds contextual mrkers to STATUS_DISPLAY_CHOICES,
TASK_DISPLAY_CHOICES and POWER_DISPLAY_CHOICES because it was impossible to
translate the stand-alone words out of context for a translator (i.e. the word
"active" will be translated differently if the active object is feminine or
masculine, since feminine and masculine depends also on the language, it is
mission impossible for the translator to translate "active" if he does not know
"what" is "active").

It is important to use unicode strings with contextual markers because of the
following django bug:
https://code.djangoproject.com/ticket/22565
The django community was very quick and responsive and fixed the bug very fast:
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/142c27218a0bb07bb197faab7b1d8eb3a084f5b9
and back-ported their fix in the 1.6 and 1.7 django branches:
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/61fd00d4fd65f44d0a05be4c7e95124e4102ec27
https://code.djangoproject.com/changeset/034866204b39f797c73997b03cd90443aa03aa91
but since in horizon we support back to django 1.4, we will have to live with
it by providing unicode strings until we drop support of old django versions.

We can't introduce contextual markers and ungettext (pluralization) verywhere
at once because Translators would totally loose their previous work. So we have
to progressively introduce contextual markers and pluralization, when a string
is changed, or for new strings. It is also the reason why this patch changes
only the strings of the instance view actions.

Since we can't use contextual markers and pluralization for all the code at
once, this patch partially:

partial-bug: 1307476

Change-Id: I4cef42dc4a12f55cf750d9a18083254c6a96e716

commit_message:
Fix IPv6 default masks for SLAAC

IETF doesn't recommend use of IPv6 networks
with masks not "/64". Recommended subnetting is
3-1-4 - 48 for provider, 16 for subnetting and
64 for network. For example SLAAC will not
work if you use subnets different from /64.
Test with port update will not work until
bug 1364166 is fixed, added attribute to it.

Change-Id: I260c820dbde1f98b569e564c7b5e7e558e431c0d

commit_message:
Allow to pass dict from resource discovery

Allowing to pass dict from resource discovery and storing it
as metadata. Before it was only possible to pass IP address,
which is not enough.
For TripleO case, important metadata like image name and flavor
from Nova are passed and stored in resource, allowing to make
aggregate queries according to them.

Change-Id: I4dabf79f248842398e1126d310d110b1fe95fad5

commit_message:
Update node details during node registration

If register-nodes is run a second time with the same set of nodes,
it will blindly try and re-register them, leading to failures from
the Nova or Ironic API. Instead, we now look for identifying marks
of registered nodes, and then update those nodes.

At the end, we check to see if there are any extra nodes registered,
and warn, possibly cleaning them up.

commit_message:
Hiding "Launch as Instance" if volume is not bootable.

If a volume which is not bootable, is used to create an instance
then the instance will go into 'Error' state.
The patch solves this issue by hiding the 'Launch as Instance'
button if the volume is not bootable.

Closes-Bug: #1327310

Change-Id: I3d9e7edf846fafab4e735d562c1ec72ad32fb220

commit_message:
Looks for variable subtitution in the same group

When we do a variable subtitution we must try to look if the option
is avialable into the same group and then into the default one for backward
compatibilty.

Otherwise variable subtitution doesn't works when we change the group of
an option and deprecated the DEFAULT group.

Change-Id: Ie5750ee028a58fba6da225a8c4b4221e23db829f
Closes-bug: #1367790

commit_message:
CLI support for queue existence and metadata operations

This patch extends the queues operation supported by the CLI.
It also renames some of the previously added features to make
them more consistent with their behaviour.

Features added:
- Check queue existence
- Set queue metadata
- Get queue metadata
- Get queue stats

Some examples:
	$ openstack queue exists myqueue
	$ openstack queue set metadata myqueue
	$ openstack queue stats myqueue

The above assumes Keystone is installed and has an endpoint
configured for Marconi. In order to bypass this in a non-Keystone
based deployment, the user can pass Marconi's url manually:

    $  openstack --os-token test
                 --os-url http://127.0.0.1:8888
		 queue exists myqueue

Change-Id: I2d8d793037470a629e52e329a17a6fed04314c3d
Partially-Implements: blueprint cli

commit_message:
Move OpenStack update timeout to the settings.py

Make update timeout setting configurable via exporting
environment variable, so it could be tuned for different
deployment scenarios. Also increase timeout value to 1 hour
by default.

Change-Id: I110d9bf1b6c8dd68d38ffc76c0185c55eee87298

commit_message:
Wait until Nailgun's API is ready after VM reset

After resetting Fuel master node we wait until 8000/tcp
port (nginx) is accepting connections. We also should wait
up to 2 minutes until Nailgun's API is ready.

Change-Id: I2360e0dab68ae0a20618f1da64ee5d6b4499e126
Closes-bug: #1368537

commit_message:
Use immutable arg rather mutable arg

Passing mutable objects as default args is a known Python pitfall.
We'd better avoid this. This commit changes mutable default args with
None, then use 'arg = arg or []'.

Change-Id: Ie036e8203deb9ab10ffb7bce1db6cda6c3672a0c

commit_message:
Do not incur the cost of a second method call

The usage of dict.get here is unnecessary since dict.setdefault will
not override an existing value.

Change-Id: Ie1b360cc7dd657aafda9f7d9de6c87cdf6c3f97d

commit_message:
Don't start keepalived service until required configuration is available

When keepalived starts with invalid config file (e.g. interface to bind to
is not set), then keepalived process generates thousands error messages into
log file and then fails anyway.

Change-Id: I1518147ce9bacedad0b735be5ec2634f9c2670ac

Ironic doesn't require these to be shutdown but leaving them running
leads to nodes running in CI from previous tests hitting the API of

are confusing when debugging problems.

"}]
commit_message:
Destroy pre existing VM's regardless of Provisioner

Ironic doesn't require these to be shutdown but leaving them running
leads to nodes running in CI from previous tests hitting the API of
services in the current test. The resulting errors and trace-backs
are confusing when debugging problems.

Change-Id: Ia5bccd69af0f92c14db901f09b32521821ba567d

Right now if assert_ostf_run_certain fails, the output is
"AssertionError: Condition was False."
which does not help much. The change makes it more verbose

commit_message:
Make assertion in assert_ostf_run_certain more verbose

Right now if assert_ostf_run_certain fails, the output is
"AssertionError: Condition was False."
which does not help much. The change makes it more verbose
giving the details of tests which must have passed but failed.

Change-Id: Iab373c3d4809e6f27147f9331f80ba03f02ae801
(cherry picked from commit beac5f49350d99167a8c797e68d78bb63501a968)

commit_message:
Remove extraneous created_iso property

The Redis driver's MessageEnvelope model has a created_iso property
that was only used in one place. This patch removes the property
and simply calls timeutils directly in the one place it is needed.

Change-Id: Icb7aab9d5e0c1e33684951bb5dc4182825f16465

commit_message:
Checking cluster status before actions

* add checking if cluster is operational or error state
  when calling an action to run OSTF tests through fuelclient
* add checking of cluster status when running network
  verification in nailgun

Change-Id: I3f40fb0e0b3d589834c242e73e9f8250daf4e05f
Closes-Bug: #1337887
Closes-Bug: #1337884

Add docs environment to tox.ini

As per the governance resolution https://review.openstack.org/119875,
projects should have a docs environment in their tox.ini testing
interface. Add one.

commit_message:
Pass instance to set_instance_error_state vs. uuid

Quick fix to patch one case in which instance.uuid was still being
passed to _set_instance_error_state when retries are disabled in
rescheduling cases.  Also updated the respective test case.

Change-Id: I24a682b926bc570d7e932ffedc664a95d41fda85
Closes-Bug: #1367342

commit_message:
Parametrizing the number of Swift replicas

Currently the number of Swift replicas is set to 1.  However most
deployments will use a replica count of 3.  We have added a
parameter SwiftReplicas with a default of 1 to allow a user to set
the replica count when creating an overcloud stack.

Change-Id: Ic676e44392786745818396dcc98cd9883a1ddd6d

commit_message:
Always revert to inital state in fake mode

* when nailgun runs in fake mode when node that belongs to cluster and
  is offline will not be completely remove when reset/delete action
* add new option `restore_offline_nodes` to `fake_tasks` decorator
  in tests to control this behavior
* fixed WebTest warning about body in DELETE request in tests from
  test_cluster_handler.py
* add test for new behavior

Change-Id: I9d400e1e8c385cd594c74d7f529e4e1fbe6d7843
Closes-Bug: #1335133

commit_message:
Fix ramdisk pkg-map for openSUSE

The package is called dhcp-client on all (open)SUSE related
distributions.

Change-Id: Iefb1bb5d0710d05699c646b86914189cb55fa033

commit_message:
Refactor ways of creating anonymous test user

Some Swift tests require random user creation to test ACL features or
prepare special data by reseller admin's requests, but that occurs
code duplication. Especially, assigning role id code was too lengthy.

This commit aggregates common codes and remove unused clean-up statements.

Change-Id: I4b965fceeec7c9cd1857375053e148d85f5f5bca

[{'created': '2014-09-10 18:38:10.000000000', 'message': "Better timeout exception in wait_for_resource_deletion

The generic rest_client.wait_for_resource_deletion
doesn't put anything into the TimeoutException that's
raised which makes it harder to debug failures.

This follows the pattern in the common waiters module
to put the test information and the resource id into
the TimeoutException message.

Change-Id: Ib0f30f15d5147aab63da35efec2f899e3ca31990
Related-Bug: #1367857
"}]
commit_message:
Better timeout exception in wait_for_resource_deletion

The generic rest_client.wait_for_resource_deletion
doesn't put anything into the TimeoutException that's
raised which makes it harder to debug failures.

This follows the pattern in the common waiters module
to put the test information and the resource id into
the TimeoutException message.

Change-Id: Ib0f30f15d5147aab63da35efec2f899e3ca31990
Related-Bug: #1367857

commit_message:
Use only one configuration file

This patch merge all the configuration file for glance-api and
glance-registry in one configuration (which should be file generated by
oslo.config.generator) and one paste configuration file (with 2
different pipelines).

Change-Id: Ia5395038daf75a7b798f85727e280fbb50deccc7

commit_message:
tests: import option before overriding it

This allow to execute test only from this file, without relying on the
side effect of other part of the code that might be loaded and therefore
define the option.

Change-Id: Id229f6fddeb49cc938bc2ae4a7c839ddf3d8633d

commit_message:
Make the extension docs a top level entry in the landing page

Currently any documentation about extensions that Keystone offers
is lacking at best. This patch moves the documentation out of the
busy configuration section, and to index/landing page.

It also provides a brief summary for each extension, and a logical
point of entry for additional information.

Change-Id: Ide8ac9b277e0fc9cab9c01073bb72fe3bc369aed

commit_message:
Add missing gettextutils _ function import

All these modules are not importable on their own because they don't
import the _ function theirself. This patch fixes that.

Change-Id: If04a53ede37932ebf812bbef8ce1f93b73a75f34

commit_message:
Expose auth methods on the adapter

Provide access to get_token, get_endpoint and invalidate to the adapter.
The adapter is essentially created per individual client and it can be
useful to know things like the endpoint that requests will be sent to
based on the parameters that are included in the endpoint_filter.

This essentially allows us to emulate the management_url and auth_token
properties of the existing clients.

Change-Id: Ic01bc52bb38e8fb72e7a6d93bfd2944b11d0b070

commit_message:
opensuse: Support pkg removal in install-packages

Add "-e" option to remove packages. This is needed for
elements/package-installs/bin/package-uninstalls which calls
"install-packages -e".

Change-Id: I673942f505d5278e6015324950f6e1455ba50805

commit_message:
Fix spelling of controller0_VLANPort

Prior to this change, using these templates fails as
controller0_VLANPort is defined, but we attempt to use
controller0VLANPort instead.

Change-Id: Ieb2eece4e7d48177acae0bef916192d8e6a4a4a3

commit_message:
Update virsh dumpxml ssh command

This patch adds a new regex for an updated virsh dumpxml ssh command.
Once Nova BM is removed we will put up patch that removes the current
dumpxml regex, but until then we will need both.

Change-Id: I10b49751d55946b8977eed3998612362c740b104

commit_message:
NSX: Correct allowed_address_pair return value on create_port

This patch fixes the NSX plugin to return [] rather than None for a
port does not have any allowed_address_pairs when a create_port api
call is made. Currently the NSX plugin is failing every patch because
now tempest is checking for this value to be [].

Change-Id: Ic82c564ff62000c367c544f44a76694be9375790
Closes-bug: 1366921

commit_message:
Add V3 JSON Home support to GET /

The server wasn't returning a JSON Home response for GET / when the
Accept header is `application/json-home`. By returning the V3 JSON
Home response for GET / a V3 client that supports JSON Home can
GET either /v3 or / and use the response. The identity API should
be able to be set to /.

Closes-Bug: #1366589
Change-Id: I3191a85acf9d2f582f6b48a164cf5ac2bf84a8cf

?Can we remove all changes of files under nova/api/openstack from this patch completely ?

@Ken'ichi - I don't see a way to do this - the issue is that as soon as you add new values to the Quota class they will be reported in the API by default.   The changes in here are to prevent that happening unless the new extension is loaded.   To do that I have to make changes in the api files.

Note though that none of the V2 API samples files change, and the tests only change to take into account the new calls to check if the extension is loaded - this shows that this patch set doesn't change the APi as such."}, {'account_id': 1501, 'date': '2014-08-22 13:39:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 21:

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-07-04 21:14:43.000000000', 'message': 'Add quotas for Server Groups

Server groups can be used to control the affinity and anti-affinity
scheduling policy for a group of servers (instances).  Whilst this is
a useful mechanism for users such scheduling decisions need to be
balanced by a deployers requirements to make effective use of the
available capacity.

This change adds quota values to constrain the number and size of
server groups a user can create.

Two new quota values are be introduced to limit the number of server
groups and the number of servers in a server group. These will follow
the existing pattern for quotas in that:

* They are defined by config values, which also include the default
  value

* They can be defined per project or per user within a project

* A value of -1 for either quota will be treated as unlimited

* Defaults can be set via the quota groups API

* Values may be changed at any time but will only take effect at the next
  server group or server create.   Reducing the quota will not affect any
  existing groups, but new servers will not be allowed into group
  that have become over quota.

Implements: blueprint server-group-quotas
DocImpact

Change-Id: Ib281e43eabfbd176454bde7f0622d46fb04fcb79

'}, {'created': '2014-08-21 16:04:49.000000000', 'message': 'Add quotas for Server Groups

Server groups can be used to control the affinity and anti-affinity
scheduling policy for a group of servers (instances).  Whilst this is
a useful mechanism for users such scheduling decisions need to be
balanced by a deployers requirements to make effective use of the
available capacity.

This change adds quota values to constrain the number and size of
server groups a user can create.

Two new quota values are be introduced to limit the number of server
groups and the number of servers in a server group. These will follow
the existing pattern for quotas in that:

* They are defined by config values, which also include the default
  value

* They can be defined per project or per user within a project

* A value of -1 for either quota will be treated as unlimited

* Defaults can be set via the quota groups API

* Values may be changed at any time but will only take effect at the next
  server group or server create.   Reducing the quota will not affect any
  existing groups, but new servers will not be allowed into group
  that have become over quota.

This is part one of a linked sequences of changes that implement the
new quotas - split to keep make the reviews easier.

This part adds the definition of the new quota values, but leaves the
V2 API unchanged.  The V3 API is updated as it shows all quota values.

The second part adds the new V2 API extension to make the new quota
values visible and changeable.  At this point a Tempest change is
required to get a clean run as it checks for a specific set of
values.

The third part implements the quota checks themselves.

Co-Author: Cyril Roelandt (Server Group Quota Unit tests)

Implements: blueprint server-group-quotas

commit_message:
Add quotas for Server Groups (V2 API compatibility & V2.1 support)

Server groups can be used to control the affinity and anti-affinity
scheduling policy for a group of servers (instances).  Whilst this is
a useful mechanism for users such scheduling decisions need to be
balanced by a deployers requirements to make effective use of the
available capacity.

This change adds quota values to constrain the number and size of
server groups a user can create.

Two new quota values are be introduced to limit the number of server
groups and the number of servers in a server group. These will follow
the existing pattern for quotas in that:

* They are defined by config values, which also include the default
  value

* They can be defined per project or per user within a project

* A value of -1 for either quota will be treated as unlimited

* Defaults can be set via the quota groups API

* Values may be changed at any time but will only take effect at the next
  server group or server create.   Reducing the quota will not affect any
  existing groups, but new servers will not be allowed into group
  that have become over quota.

This is part one of a linked sequences of changes that implement the
new quotas - split to make the reviews easier.

This part adds the definition of the new quota values, but leaves the
V2 API unchanged.  The V2.1 API is updated as it shows all quota values.

The second part adds the new V2 API extension to make the new quota
values visible and changeable.  At this point a Tempest change is
required to get a clean run as it checks for a specific set of
values.

The third part implements the quota checks themselves.

Thanks to Cyril Roelandt for supplying some of the unit tests.

Co-authored-by: Cyril Roelandt <cyril.roelandt@enovance.com>

Implements: blueprint server-group-quotas
DocImpact

Change-Id: Ib281e43eabfbd176454bde7f0622d46fb04fcb79

commit_message:
Improve the selectability of Swift tests

Before this commit, Tempest tests of Swift were selectable only for WSGI
middleware on proxy servers. With this commit, other following Swift
functions are also selectable with Tempest's config file.

Following Swift functions are selectable now:
 - Old-style Container Sync: mirroring objects in the container to another
   container
 - Object Versioning: versioning all objects in the container
 - Discoverability: providing details about the Swift installation

Implements blueprint more-selectable-swift-tests

commit_message:
Added new filter class for sub-service tables

The same filter class was being run on almost every system info table
despite them having different attributes which was causing horizon to
break. New filter class filters on the 'binary' attribute of the
cinder and nova sub-services.

Change-Id: Idc69a58ee4705280e44bc81bcd429c58da00e6f1
Closes-Bug: 1363250

commit_message:
Sync jsonutils from oslo-incubator 32e7f0b5

Syncs the jsonutils module from oslo-incubator using commit
32e7f0b56f527427544050f251999f3de588ac93 .

Note that since there's a feature change in oslo-incubator I'm
switching to module syncs.

 $ ./update.sh --nodeps --base keystone --dest-dir ../keystone \
     --modules jsonutils

This change includes the following commit
-----------------------------------------
d9060f6 Check for namedtuple_as_object support before using it

Change-Id: I152faacdbb394209f87b91a699bb4ca185c2125e
Closes-Bug: #1361230

commit_message:
Allow swift "min_part_hours" to be configurable

With swift rings, a "min_part_hours" value is required. This is the
time (in hours) before a specific partition can be moved in succession
(following a rebalance). Currently this value is hard-coded to 1 but
this value is not feasible for a large system and it can often take
several hours for partitions to re-align following a rebalance.

Therefore, this change allows this value to be configurable by adding
the "MIN_PART_HOURS" variable. If this change is accepted, I will add
the relevant parameter in tripleo-heat-templates.

Change-Id: Ie6438386a54794e1ae2f31ad925db01c2c10ed6d

commit_message:
Retype the volume with correct empty QoS

Currently for storwzie driver, if the new type does not have QoS
configurations, the old QoS configurations remain in the volume after retyping
it. It should be retyped into a volume with empty QoS.

Change-Id: I417ca06a74c9c8c6dc840f2fd348292073bd5ddf
Closes-Bug: #1368595

HTTP return code.

commit_message:
javelin: fix object destruction

When adding "destroy" support in javelin, a wrong condition has been
introduced to validate if an object has been destroyed or not by its
HTTP return code.

204 is returned and was considered as an error, which is wrong.
Also, delete a resource cleanup dupplication (servers).

Change-Id: I1adaf143ebf2de90d1b2cafc91dcd3a521b96fec
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

When we used the i18n markers (_, _LE, _LW, etc) from
ironic.openstack.common.gettextutils, we bypassed H302
hacking rule for them (via tox.ini file). Now that we've
converted to using the markers from oslo.i18n and are no

Closes-Bug: #1368425
"}]
commit_message:
Remove bypassing of H302 for gettextutils markers

When we used the i18n markers (_, _LE, _LW, etc) from
ironic.openstack.common.gettextutils, we bypassed H302
hacking rule for them (via tox.ini file). Now that we've
converted to using the markers from oslo.i18n and are no
longer using the markers from gettextutils, we can remove
the bypass stuff.

Change-Id: I26147b69884cd9c075e1cfe38a92e38e861083e7
Closes-Bug: #1368425

commit_message:
Add sort_key and sort_dir parameters to *-list

These arguments are using for sorting the result on the server.
Small refactoring was conducted to seperate processing of
common arguments for all lists into the utility function.

Change-Id: I33be1fcecc665c8f2207e53b24ff47954d80dc60
Closes-Bug: #1339731

commit_message:
Remove workaround for Ubuntu kernel permissions

Without the dependency on python-guestfs in Icehouse, we no
longer need to provide a workaround for Ubuntu kernel
permission issues on compute nodes.

Change-Id: Ib1d5225c138b1d9d63948b587ff53daded010100
Closes-Bug: #1343738

Fix host listing in live migration

The live migration selector needs to offer a list
of hosts, not a list of hypervisors.

Closes-Bug: #1335999

commit_message:
Extra unit tests for check_delete_headers

A few extra tests to verify check_delete_headers in
constraints.py. A little duplication of coverage of existing
proxy/controllers/test_obj.py:TestObjController.test_POST_delete_at
but these tests call the recently refactored function directly,
and also add tests for X-Delete-After taking precedence over
X-Delete-At.

Change-Id: I129cef15a6feac8a60fd4efbb3535d93f0eaab36

ok, so ignore everything said I said about "is there a client facing behavior change" - there definitely is not.  Although I should write up some of the behaviors I observed from eventlet.wsgi because where we're at is sorta whack; and I'm not sure how it'd all play out with other wsgi servers.

I'm not we have a clean delimitation between what swob should validate and what constraints should validate - so you may have to dismiss my personal opinion here, but...

It seems like swob should really restrict itself to raising errors along the lines of "this is invalid http as I understand the specification" and anything closer to "this particular swift wsgi application doesn't want to handle this type of otherwise valid http request" could be pulled out to constraints.

e.g. proxy requires content-length unless it's chunked - even though http and most wsgi servers are fine with a PUT that indicates the end of the message with Connection: close - we want to return 411 in this case.  Good candidate for constraints; but me thinks less helpful jammed down into swob?

I can certainly live with this if it get's merged, but I'd prefer the 411 come back out of swob into constraints where it was and leave message_length alone for now?'}, {'account_id': 9625, 'date': '2014-08-22 00:48:27.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

commit_message:
Fix rootwrap for non openstack.org iqn's

The encryption methods implemented for attached volumes
require a symbolic link created to the /dev/disk-by* iqn.

The current implementation works fine for LVM, however the rootwrap
is restricted to only allow iqns of the form openstack.org, for
vendors that use their own target and iqn this won't work and will
result in the attach failing for unauthorized command.

This just makes the regex for the rootwrap filter a bit more
permissive, only looking for iscsi-iqn.*

Change-Id: I023ad24867c045a88f72c5ac7ac4e4da097a3643
Closes-Bug: 1362854

commit_message:
LDAP: refactor use of "1.1" OID

I've noticed several people asking questions about the arbitrary usage
of ['1.1'] in code review, so I figured I'd refactor them into a
constant so it's a bit more self-documenting, since it's definition is,
in fact, completely arbitrary:

    If the client does not want any attributes returned, it can specify
    a list containing only the attribute with OID "1.1". This OID was
    chosen arbitrarily and does not correspond to any attribute in use.

Source: http://www.alvestrand.no/objectid/1.1.html

Change-Id: Ib2901bd8593b5a6ea8b6a5488f0d45b51fa8b77c

translation of strings, as documented at
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LoggingStandards#Log_Translation

- add log translation hints for warning, error and info levels
- move from LOG.warning to LOG.warn
- remove use of % as a string formatter, use the log functionality
  instead

Partial implements blueprint log-translation-hints

commit_message:
Log translation hint for Heat.api

Currently, Log translation is motivated by oslo's move to prioritized
translation of strings, as documented at
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/LoggingStandards#Log_Translation

- add log translation hints for warning, error and info levels
- move from LOG.warning to LOG.warn
- remove use of % as a string formatter, use the log functionality
  instead

Partial implements blueprint log-translation-hints

Change-Id: Ie17871f42f75085c2ac6a14fb1526df7bc3a9603

commit_message:
Reduce unused tox environments

Since the openstack-ci only tests 5 of the many tox enviroments
we had listed and from my knowledge nobody else is testing using
those other non-standard enviroments just reduce the set of applicable
environments to the ones that are being used (which also means we
can remove the usage of toxgen and just stick with a simpler file
that is easier to use, modify and adjust).

Change-Id: I4d2302594b9f9e8741f9693cb358efc1418bd45d

commit_message:
Fix service groups with zookeeper

Service groups using zookeeper don't work due to apparently improper
handling of the zookeeper session creation.

No additional unit tests as the mocking these interfaces probably
doesn't actually provide substantial future guaruntees. The correct
long term fix is to enable zk for unit testing upstream.

Change-Id: I21691843cb4936d10a0b82df41aef3afe5bf2519
Closes-bug: #1239864

commit_message:
Allow adding or changing the CSS classes of a data table

Sometimes a datatable needs to be displayed slightly differently, for
instance with or without the borders, condensed, zebra, etc. This patch
lets us do that in two ways.

It adds a css_class option to table's Meta, so that we can easily add
more classes to a particular table, and modify its looks with CSS.

It also puts the whole table's CSS class list in a block, so that we
can inherit from the table's template to completely replace its classes,
if we need to.

Change-Id: I64a1f3ba8d80643c545de024f52ec3313bbff8e5

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-05 05:25:55.000000000', 'message': 'Fix boto tests network tear-down issues

In [1] I have identified that the boto tests aren't actually running
on Ubuntu due to an error creating the boot images which is undetected
as a failure by devstack.  However, I can not get this change in, as
tempest.thirdparty.boto.test_ec2_instance_run.InstanceRunTest keeps
failing in tearDownClass() due to:

    "Unable to complete operation on subnet [...]. One or more ports
    have an IP allocation from this subnet"

Full logs at [2].  What I did notice, however, was that this test
works on Fedora 20 [3].  The difference there is that setUpClass() was
*not* creating the isolated network resources (grep [2] & [3] for
InstanceRunTest:setUpClass)

I can not really explain why on Ubuntu the isolated network gets
created as part of class setup, and on Fedora it doesn't.  However,
the correct thing to do seems to be to explicitly not create it.

Closes-Bug: #1365831

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/113767/
[2] http://logs.openstack.org/67/113767/1/check/check-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full/f7610f8/logs/tempest.txt.gz
[3] http://logs.openstack.org/39/112739/1/check/check-tempest-dsvm-f20/6781e53/logs/tempest.txt.gz

Change-Id: I626aa32c49233a1c9b59cd471ce4c2860431bd9e

commit_message:
Skip boto instance test with neutron

In [1] I have identified that the boto tests aren't actually running
on Ubuntu due to an error creating the boot images which is undetected
as a failure by devstack.  However, I can not get this change in, as
tempest.thirdparty.boto.test_ec2_instance_run.InstanceRunTest keeps
failing in tearDownClass() due to:

    "Unable to complete operation on subnet [...]. One or more ports
    have an IP allocation from this subnet"

Full logs at [2].  While we are working on this, skip this test on
neutron so other tests don't futher bit-rot

Partial-Bug: #1365831

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/113767/
[2] http://logs.openstack.org/67/113767/1/check/check-tempest-dsvm-neutron-full/f7610f8/logs/tempest.txt.gz

Change-Id: I626aa32c49233a1c9b59cd471ce4c2860431bd9e

This fix changes the behaviour of the the "Upload Object" button for Swift to
be enabled by default. There was a check to disable the button if there were
no user changes, but that does not make too much sense since you can only upload
an object if you explicitly change the name of the object.

Closes-Bug: #1367093

commit_message:
Enable upload object button without user input.

This fix changes the behaviour of the the "Upload Object" button for Swift to
be enabled by default. There was a check to disable the button if there were
no user changes, but that does not make too much sense since you can only upload
an object if you explicitly change the name of the object.

Change-Id: Ib2d14bec55d858dbc82981336a4373a87bf876e0
Closes-Bug: #1367093

commit_message:
Increase CEPH_LOOPBACK_DISK_SIZE_DEFAULT to 4GB

CEPH_LOOPBACK_DISK_SIZE_DEFAULT should be more than 2GB
to make volume snapshot feature works. 2GB is not enough
because min Cinder volume size is 1GB and no snapshot
could be created.

This also fixes related Tempest tests and experimental
check-tempest-dsvm-full-ceph gate job.

Change-Id: Ifa41d0d1764d68ea02dcb32a5fc62f7f6282904d

commit_message:
Test against latest glance_store code

Install glance_store from git so we can test Glance against master. This
is useful for both, glance and glance_store gates, to make sure nothing
is broken there.

Change-Id: I6c01165c4384c41f46f2c32d64475703b3178dab

commit_message:
Install non deprecated DB for Cloudera Manager

Cloudera Manager installation guide recommend install
'cloudera-manager-server-db-2' package.
Link for doc: http://goo.gl/r7mCcV

Closes-bug: #1360313

Change-Id: Ic3c899ffb4a925f5285ed1c150e6333cf7a949ea

commit_message:
Remove binding:profile update from Mellanox ML2 MD

Remove temporary work-around that populates physical_network in
binding:profile. Now when both neutron and nova use binding:vif_details
to pass attributes to plug neutron port, this work-around is not nequired.
Remove related temporary code from ML2 plugin.

Change-Id: Ib37203af396f31080b1b27b500a571c20917f5a4
Closes-Bug: 1360762

remove quantum leftovers from docs

- all OCF resource agents in our fuel-library are called
  neutron-aget-[dhcp|l3|metadata|ovs], so rename corresponding
  resources to reflect current code behaviour

Ok my concern here is where did the new format come from, where did the old format come from, and how do we know that *both* formats aren't valid, based on different database driver versions or MySQL versions?  Does the regex here perhaps work with the older format as well (and can we leave those tests in)?"}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2014-08-24 13:03:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Old format came from a StackOverflow comment someone pointed me too.

New format come from me trying to make this work with MySQL in a real application.


So I'm pretty confident about what I'm doing here. ;)"}, {'account_id': 11816, 'date': '2014-08-25 16:44:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

OK but MySQL versions and client library versions change.   Is it the case that this feature has never worked at all?   How did these original exception messages get merged then, why was this added without any real world observations?'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2014-08-26 09:27:17.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

> OK but MySQL versions and client library versions change. Is it the case that this feature has never worked at all?

AFAIK no, the patch is very recent and it's the first release with it.

> How did these original exception messages get merged then, why was this added without any real world observations?

See history at https://review.openstack.org/#/c/94333/ if you're curious I guess."}, {'account_id': 7491, 'date': '2014-08-26 11:22:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Julien,

so maybe we should re-write these tests to use real backends?'}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2014-08-26 12:06:33.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Victor, that would be really great. Is there an easy way to do that right now? I'm not so familiar with the tests in oslo.db yet. Any pointer?"}, {'account_id': 7491, 'date': '2014-08-26 14:34:50.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Julien, 

I'd like to propose something like this - http://paste.openstack.org/show/100486/
It's quick-and-dirty example, but I suppose, that it shows the main idea - OpportunisticTestCase's to get engine, which was connected to the real backend."}, {'account_id': 11816, 'date': '2014-08-26 14:39:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

We should add these new opportunistic tests, but also leave the existing "self-contained" ones as is.  The existing ones have the value that they can run against arbitrary exception messages that might not be easy to have available within test environments.    I don't know that it's the case here, but the format of these messages *do* change sometimes across new server versions or new client library versions.'}, {'account_id': 7491, 'date': '2014-08-26 14:57:10.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Fix DBReferenceError on MySQL and SQLite

It turns out the test was wrong as the error message used was not a good
one. Real world tests showed that, so I've updated the test and the code
to work.

Refactored tests to use real backends, fix error message for SQLite.

Co-Authored-By: Victor Sergeyev <vsergeyev@mirantis.com>

Change-Id: Ifa64478a9ac9ed0a3c317a8974615b770c85f313

commit_message:
Configure the stores explicitly

The store configure() method is being called two times: on one hand
in the store constructor and also explicitly in the create_stores()
method.

Since the configure() method can contain remote calls, it is better
to avoid calling it more than once, especially, when it doesn't add
any value.

Change-Id: I6f39dfa7fd3d0ef7ff4fc2a9ebbebdfb0cf114a1

The old logging statements in lockutils made for some confusing log
entries where it would appear a given lock was acquired multiple
times by different threads at the same time.  See referenced bug
for details.

In order to alleviate that confusion, this change does a few things:
1) Adds an explicit "acquired" message inside the lock so it is
   clear when the lock was actually acquired.
2) Moves the release message inside the semaphore so there's no
   chance of it being logged out of order.
3) Removes the "Got semaphore" message and splits it into two
   separate messages depending on whether the semaphore was found
   in the weakref dictionary.  Making it clear which code path
   was followed should help with future debugging.

This is the incubator port of olso.concurrency change

commit_message:
Clarify logging in lockutils

The old logging statements in lockutils made for some confusing log
entries where it would appear a given lock was acquired multiple
times by different threads at the same time.  See referenced bug
for details.

In order to alleviate that confusion, this change does a few things:
1) Adds an explicit "acquired" message inside the lock so it is
   clear when the lock was actually acquired.
2) Moves the release message inside the semaphore so there's no
   chance of it being logged out of order.
3) Removes the "Got semaphore" message and splits it into two
   separate messages depending on whether the semaphore was found
   in the weakref dictionary.  Making it clear which code path
   was followed should help with future debugging.

This is the incubator port of olso.concurrency change
I0fbb473c60d48c9704597d9e3634402857861a66

Change-Id: If863c9d3896bc786f3c9c46196ebb0766e57d863
Closes-Bug: 1367941

commit_message:

commit_message:
Add /var/run security contexts to host_info.txt

An incorrect security context in /var/run can cause SELinux issue.
A listing of the /var/run directory with security contexts is
added to host_info.txt to aid debugging.

Change-Id: I93b74c88d6250cbf5eec9304f057e3858d2fcf5b

commit_message:
Use a new style of semaphore container to see if this fixes

Instead of using a weakref dictionary use a customized container
that we clean up as we consume new semaphores that also has attached
methods to determine when a weak reference is destroyed.

commit_message:
Set revoke_api attribute to None on provider object

When an optional extension such as revoke_api is not
included in the pipeline.  Keystone was not setting the attribute to None.
This resulted in validate call raising the following error:

    AttributeError: 'Provider' object has no attribute 'revoke_api'

Change-Id: I15fe304f759cafb6cc5637ede0529571274b4fe0
Closes-bug: #1315049

commit_message:
Adds log statements in multiprocess API test

Adds a bunch of INFO logging in the multiprocess API test so that we can
perhaps get some better information to debug with when a timeout
actually occurs for bug #1357578.

Renames the _terminate_workers() method to _wait_for_workers_to_end(),
as that accurately describes what that method was really doing, and adds
a new _terminate_workers() method to actually stop the
workers (used in tearDown() when the test_restart_sighup() method does
not actually stop the API worker processes like the other test methods
do).

Change-Id: I83731fcaeb9265fc46472ef3a505d1184d44bfe8

commit_message:
Load cfg params conditionally

Some datastores don't support config groups so this should be
conditional.

Also, tightened search by version name.

Change-Id: I2b37ce2e30c2e23b8291cd65c883fd2caadabdad
Closes-Bug: #1366939

commit_message:
Friendly error message while creating security group

Validate parameters before going to the parser, while
creating security group. Before that, there was an
error about no such parameter.

Closes-Bug: #977192
Change-Id: I159f9c435f832b1476cda09280e4eeb0cca03e52

commit_message:
Adding a periodic task to remove zombie proxy users

Changes
* adding periodic task for user removal
* adding a wrapper function for the periodic tasks class to improve
  configuration
* refactoring proxy user delete function to allow a user id

Change-Id: I641e1650e7a5fcd96246e13b7e1d548c4a0dda25
Partial-implements: blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication

commit_message:
Refactoring DataSources to use proxy user

Changes
* adding constants for trust id and domain name to swift_helper
* refactoring oozie edp workflows to use proxy configs when necessary
* adding tests to exercise proxy domain usage in workflows
* removing credentials requirement for DataSource models when using
  proxy domain
* pruning duplicate MapReduce test
* adding tests for DataSource creation without credentials
* adding Keystone v3 token endpoint to Hadoop core-site.xml when domain
  requested

Partial-implements: blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication
Change-Id: I38fd1c470d608c3de9d8c140228d7c9666523b23

commit_message:
Adding trust delegation and removal for proxy users

Changes
* adding a generic keystone client creation function
* adding a function to create proxy user clients
* renaming admin client functions for clarity
* adding token delegation/removal during proxy user creation/deletion
* adding a configuration option for proxy user trust roles

Change-Id: I362a27c1b1d0c5b81d6fbbb91fc0689e339f0076
Partial-implements: blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication

commit_message:
Adding proxy user creation per job execution

Changes
* adding sahara.utils.proxy module
* adding functions to create and delete proxy users
* adding proxy user creation during job execution
* adding proxy user deletion during job execution status update
* adding sanitization for proxy configs from job execution
* adding unit test for proxy usage detection function

Partial-implements: blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication
Change-Id: I551a14a3cb5320a27fc6104b35c3b9a08a03abda

commit_message:
Adding configuration and check for proxy domain

Changes
* adding configuration option for use of proxy domain
* adding configuration option for proxy domain name
* adding method to get the Domain object for the proxy

Partial-implements: blueprint edp-swift-trust-authentication
Change-Id: I369de80c918a52db5200865f754c40bc807289e4

commit_message:
Keystone local authenticate has an unnecessary pending audit record.

Pending should be used for long running operations but local
authenticate is not such an operation.

Change-Id: If06c826c912a973cf133c6dcc6dabe77a392c64a
Closes-Bug: #1366991

commit_message:
List resources with detail

This commit adds support for getting a list of ports, chassis, ports
associated with a node and nodes associated with a chassis with all
attributes, to both the client and the shell CLI.

Closes-Bug: #1366866
Change-Id: If1941de66d70cdbcc3f31cefdbcd4f634e6ce24e

Document glance v2 commands

The glance v2 commands need to be called as:
glance -os-image-api-version 2 CMD

Implement logic for this and enhance output.
Closes-Bug: #1367430

commit_message:
Update fedora-rdo-icehouse element

This patch takes advantage of the refactoring of the rdo-icehouse
and enable-packages-install bits.  The reactoring allows other
redhat family os elements also use rdo-icehouse and
enable-packages-install.

This patch also deprecates the fedora-rdo-icehouse-repository element
and removes the dependency on it from fedora-rdo-icehouse.

Change-Id: I4e2391d987a05163bc7d45ad03f80c9f6d555681

commit_message:
Add hooks to workaround patching bugs

Add several pre and post patching hooks and tests
for them.

* Stop or migrate corosync services from controller node
  and return them after the deployment

* Stop openstack services and kill pids that was
  not stopped together with their children

* Remove openstack packages before deployment
  to prevent conflicts during the update and rollback

Change-Id: Icfc17308d955e55b5e5b31a9c17e0b6d13d8ba10
Closes-bug: #1364081
Closes-bug: #1365635
Closes-bug: #1364068
Co-Authored-By: Vladimir Sharshov <vsharshov@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>
Co-Authored-By: Vladimir Kuklin <vkuklin@mirantis.com>

When using the VirtualBox additions, there is a chance that after the
vboxadd service has started, the shared directory is not yet fully
available. In that case, activate_autostart.sh is never run (although
it may appear in time to be deleted).

'}]
commit_message:
labs: fix race in preseed script

When using the VirtualBox additions, there is a chance that after the
vboxadd service has started, the shared directory is not yet fully
available. In that case, activate_autostart.sh is never run (although
it may appear in time to be deleted).

This patch makes the script from preseed wait for activate_autostart.sh
to become available before it tries to execute it.

Change-Id: I1c2f3ef2f4301f36efec8a70b811ffe97dbaa779

commit_message:
Remove absolute path in KillFilter for metadata-proxy

This commit fix the problem of killing neutron-ns-metadata-proxy
when running in Virtual Environment.

Change-Id: I987dd87e19c218846a48e58b61679b4153d97f66
Closes-bug: #1363773

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-10 23:58:23.000000000', 'message': 'Add transactional test support to provisioning

This patch further reorganizes ProvisionedDatabase
such that it now can maintain a single ProvisionedDatabase
instance across a named "scope".  A "scope" refers
to a series of test runs which can all safely share the
same database schema as well as optional fixture data.

When a test specifies a non-None "scope", the test
is run within a special context that redirects
engine and connection use to a new series of objects
based on a hierarchy called NonCommittingConnectable.
This object produces a facade that behaves like
SQLAlchemy Engine, Connection and Transaction objects
to the degree necessary for a typical database round-trip
test, but ensures that all operations run within a
single transaction that is never committed.   To allow
tests to do real rollbacks, savepoints are used, and the
transaction container always maintains a savepoint
as well for this purpose.

As tests run, if each successive test indicates the
same "scope" as the previous, the database is not dropped,
and the same schema is re-used; all changes to this schema
since the last test ran will have been rolled back.

When a change in scope occurs between tests, the
"drop all objects" routine is run, again so that the
database is not actually dropped, but is instead cleared
of all objects built within it.

Currently, the behavior of ProvisionedDatabase
as a persistent object between tests is only meaningful within
the span of a testr run that calls upon the
testr "instance_execute" and related hooks.  If these
hooks are not called, such as if the tests are run
via a different test runner, or from testtools directly,
there is currently no way for the
provisioning system to have an indication to drop
databases when all tests are complete, so without
instance_execute setting up OSLO_SCHEMA_TOKEN, the
old behavior of dropping the named database after
each test still takes place.  The ProvisionedDatabase
instance ties its own lifecycle to that of the named database
which it creates; so when dropping the database, the
ProvisionedDatabase itself removes it from the lookup.
On the next lookup for that type of database, a new
ProvisionedDatabase will replace it.

The default scope for any test is None, which
indicates that the scoping feature is not used for
those tests.  However, assuming testr has specified
OSLO_SCHEMA_TOKEN, the ProvisionedDatabase instance is now
persistent across runs for these tests as well, but at
the end of each test it now runs the "drop all objects"
routine, rather than dropping the whole database.

Partial-Bug: #1339206
Change-Id: I3bca012e2c7655b60cde7085ea55df365219edba

based on a hierarchy called NonCommittingConnectable.
This object produces a facade that behaves like
SQLAlchemy Engine, Connection and Transaction objects
to the degree necessary for a typical database round-trip
test, but ensures that all operations run within a
single transaction that is never committed.   To allow
tests to do real rollbacks, savepoints are used, and the
transaction container always maintains a savepoint
as well for this purpose.

As tests run, if each successive test indicates the
same "scope" as the previous, the database is not dropped,
and the same schema is re-used; all changes to this schema
since the last test ran will have been rolled back.

When a change in scope occurs between tests, the
"drop all objects" routine is run, again so that the
database is not actually dropped, but is instead cleared
of all objects built within it.

Currently, the behavior of ProvisionedDatabase
as a persistent object between tests is only meaningful within
the span of a testr run that calls upon the
testr "instance_execute" and related hooks.  If these
hooks are not called, such as if the tests are run
via a different test runner, or from testtools directly,
there is currently no way for the
provisioning system to have an indication to drop
databases when all tests are complete, so without
instance_execute setting up OSLO_SCHEMA_TOKEN, the
old behavior of dropping the named database after
each test still takes place.  The ProvisionedDatabase
instance ties its own lifecycle to that of the named database
which it creates; so when dropping the database, the
ProvisionedDatabase itself removes it from the lookup.

ProvisionedDatabase will replace it.

The default scope for any test is None, which
indicates that the scoping feature is not used for
those tests.  However, assuming testr has specified
OSLO_SCHEMA_TOKEN, the ProvisionedDatabase instance is now
persistent across runs for these tests as well, but at
the end of each test it now runs the "drop all objects"
